I like building small, focused tools in Zig.

Most of my projects target constrained environments — low memory, minimal dependencies, fast startup. Things like terminal emulators, window managers, and multiplexers where every byte counts.

## Interests

- Systems programming with Zig
- Terminal and TUI applications
- Window management and desktop environments
- Browser engine internals
- Embedded / low-resource computing (RPi Zero, etc.)

## Philosophy

Keep it simple. Keep it small. If the standard library already does it, don't reinvent it. If you can do it without a dependency, do.
